From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Add binary-level locale override flag

Detection vector: navigator.language and Accept-Language headers must
agree. If they differ, detection sites flag the browser as suspicious.
JS-level locale overrides can be detected by checking the property
descriptor on Navigator.prototype.language.

This patch adds a --ab-locale=<BCP47> flag that sets the locale at
the ICU level, ensuring all locale sources agree.

Surface: intl
Closes: locale inconsistency between JS and HTTP layers

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/language.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/language.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ AtomicString DefaultLanguage() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: if --ab-locale=<BCP47> is set, use it instead
+  // of the system locale. This ensures navigator.language,
+  // Accept-Language headers, and Intl APIs all report the same value.
+  if (!ab_locale_.empty()) {
+    return AtomicString(ab_locale_.c_str());
+  }
